---
title: Beany Zucchini Quesadillas with Lime Crema, Romaine Salad, and Southwestern Spices
description: Cumin and chili powder bring a one-two punch of spice and smokiness to these jam-packed veggie quesadillas. But worry not—the tangy lime crema and refreshingly crisp romaine salad help cool things off. You’ll practice filling and toasting quesadillas until they’re irresistibly warm and melty, then delight as they drip with cheesy goodness in your hands.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/beany-zucchini-quesadillas-d04d80ac.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/beany-zucchini-quesadillas-40b6f195.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beany-zucchini-quesadillas-5964ec502310a83fad68b651
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 24 g
  sodium: 1020 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 200 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly
slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise
and slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Zest @lime{1} until you have ½ tsp, then
cut into halves. Thinly slice @romaine lettuce{1}(thinly sliced). Core and dice
@roma tomato{1}(cored and diced). Mice @jalapeño{1}(minced, ribs and seeds
removed).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
onion and cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Remove from pan and
set aside. Add zucchini and another drizzle of @olive oil{} to pan. Cook,
tossing, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Meanwhile, drain and rinse
@black beans{1%box}.

Return onion to pan along with tomato, @southwest spice blend{½%tbsp},
black beans, and @chipotle powder{1%tsp} and jalapeño to taste. Cook, tossing,
until tomato is softened, ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove
from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

In a small bowl, stir together @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @lime zest{½%tsp}.

Add one @flour tortillas{6} to same pan over medium heat. Sprinkle one half with
a bit of @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}, then top with a little filling. Sprinkle with
a little more mozzarella, then fold tortilla over to create a quesadilla. Cook
until tortilla is crispy and cheese melts, about ~{3%minutes} per side. Transfer
to a #baking sheet{} and place in oven to keep warm. Repeat with remaining
tortillas.

Toss lettuce, a squeeze of lime juice, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a
medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Cut quesadillas into wedges. Serve with
salad and crema on the side.

> Cumin and chili powder bring a one-two punch of spice and smokiness to these
> jam-packed veggie quesadillas. The tangy lime crema and refreshingly crisp
> romaine salad help cool things off. You'll practice filling and toasting
> quesadillas until they're irresistibly warm and melty, then delight as they
> drip with cheesy goodness in your hands.